caption: A friend of mine had brought me a chicken patty from this spot a couple weeks ago and as soon as I had my first bite, I knew I had to come back. It was so good!! When I arrived around 315 on a Tuesday afternoon, the restaurant was empty. I waited at the counter for a few moments until someone came from the kitchen to take my order. The woman was friendly and efficient. I ordered a small jerk chicken meal with rice and peas, cabbage and a chicken patty on the side. I waited not even 5 minutes for my order to be prepared. When I arrived home with my to go order, a mere 5 min later, all of the food was still warm. The bite of cabbage with a little bit of plaintains and chicken was the delicious! The rice was flavorful but it was a bit dry. The rice and peas were definitely not fresh, which is understandable considering the off peak time that I went, but still disappointing. The chicken could have been more tender and I would've appreciate more sauce BUT the flavor is on point. Overall, everything tasted really well but the texture could be improved a bit for some things. I will definitely go back again, but perhaps closer to the peak hours in hopes of fresher rice!

When I lived close I used to frequent here once, sometimes twice a week. The food was always good. When my location and eating habits changed I stopped going to many places including Andrene's so, me not having visited here in many years wasn't anything personal. However when I visited today I saw the renovations and changes for the first time. In greeting Andrene herself expressing that I haven't been here in a while, she seemed to get an immediate attitude and acted very cavalier towards me while I was with my 11 year old daughter. She stated "having moved from the area is no excuse to not have come, I have customers from Delaware" which her tone was rude but I was willing to excuse. But when I also mentioned I have been taking care of a sick parent and hadn't gone to a lot of places recently,  her response was "I have a sick Mother too on dialysis and I work a full time job and run a business so?" Her body language and tone turned me way off. Look , if I haven't been there in years, I haven't...that's no reason to cop an attitude with me for it.  All customers matter albeit regular, loyal, first time, or returning customers. I shouldn't have to experience a snippy attitude and a cavalier response to the why's and whats. Thanks for the beef patties (which are premade anyway) Andrene but never will I walk in your place again. It's easy to forget that America provides opportunity but also choice. Your spot isn't the only place providing authentic Jamaican food.
